 The Nigeria Army, 82 Division, has urged those living near its shooting range to remain calm during the exercise. The shooting exercise is billed to commence on Wednesday, May 4, as the Nigeria Army begins camping at the headquarters of the 14 Brigade in Ohafia, Abia State. According to a statement by the 14 Brigade Public Relations Officer, Lieut. Innocent Omale, the exercise would last for two weeks. The statement read that the exercise would feature firing of live ammunition at the range site. It further read, ”The exercise is to prepare contingents of 82 Division for the forthcoming shooting competition with other Divisions soon.” It urged members of the public, especially people in communities around the barracks, not to panic when they hear sounds of gun shots. It also urged farmers to keep off from the area for the period of the exercise. 